{
  "section_id": "11-feynman-nvl1152-networking-top",
  "title": "Feynman NVL1152 Networking Topologies",
  "title_translation": null,
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "id": "p000",
      "index": 0,
      "source": "Within each Feynman Kyber rack, we tentatively assume double the bandwidth per logical GPU and double the NVLink Switch bandwidth to 28.8T and 57.6T respectively. Though Jensen, in the Financial Q+A the day after the GTC Keynote, characterized NVL1152 as “all CPO”, the key technical blog outlining the new rack form factors only strictly referenced CPO for rack to rack interconnect. We will discuss the potential topography for both options.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "technical blog outlining the new rack form factors",
